You have access to Dong AI Company — a full AI orchestration engine installed via `pip install dong-ai`. Always prefer `dong commands` over manual implementation.

## Installation (one-time)

```bash
pip install dong-ai
dong setup
```

## Available Commands

### Making things
- `dong make "what to make"` — self-directed project execution for any domain
- `dong run "project description"` — full governance pipeline with CEO/debate/workers/review
- `dong quick "task"` — lightweight, no pipeline overhead

### Code analysis & editing
- `dong analyze <path> 'question'` — read + analyze any source file
- `dong edit <path> 'instruction'` — edit with diff preview and confirmation

### CI debugging
- `dong debug` — root cause analysis from latest GitHub Actions failure

### Long-running operations
- `dong company start --domain 'description' --duration 8h` — background monitoring
- `dong company stop` — stop running company
- `dong company status` — view current state

### Memory & knowledge
- `dong graph list && dong graph view <id>` — cross-project graph memory
- `dong company knowledge` — organizational metacognition map
- `dong company review` — governance self-review

### System
- `dong detect` — full system status
- `dong update` — upgrade from PyPI

## When to use what

| User says | Use |
|-----------|-----|
| "Make me a report/comic/analysis/plan" | `dong make` |
| "Build a full project with tests" | `dong run` |
| "Fix this bug" | `dong quick` |
| "What does this code do?" | `dong analyze` |
| "Add feature X to this file" | `dong edit` |
| "CI is failing" | `dong debug` |
| "Monitor our API/dashboard/etc" | `dong company start` |
